  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through several key approaches:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Regulations\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for cash transactions\n\n2. Investigative Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing financial transactions\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Use of advanced data analytics\n\n3. Criminal Prosecution\n- Charging individuals with money laundering offenses\n- Seizure of illegally obtained assets\n- Potential imprisonment and financial penalties\n\n4. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations across jurisdictions\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight\n- Government agencies monitoring financial activities\n- Compliance requirements for banks and financial institutions\n- Regular audits and reporting mechanisms\n\nThese strategies aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and investigative approaches.",
